<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Main Menu Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="CSS/stylesheet.css">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">

    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.16.0/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
<div class="jumbotron text-center">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-2">

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-8">
            <h1>Welcome to Online Checkers!</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-2">
            <a href="loginPage.ejs">Sign in or Sign up</a>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="container-fluid text-center">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-3">
            <h4>Tutorial</h4>
            <h5>Moving the pieces</h5>
            <p>There are two different types of moves available in Checkers.</p>
            <p class="smallText">
                1. Simple move: A simple move consists of moving a piece one square diagonally to an adjacent unoccupied dark square. Regular pieces can move diagonally forward only; King pieces can move in any diagonal direction.
            </p>
            <p class="smallText">
                2. Jump: A jump consists of moving a piece that is diagonally adjacent an opponent's piece, to an empty square immediately beyond it in the same direction (thus "jumping over" the opponent's piece front and back ). Regular pieces can jump diagonally forward only; King pieces can jump in any diagonal direction. A jumped piece is considered "captured" and removed from the game.
            </p>
            <p class="smallText">Jumping is always mandatory: if a player has the option to jump, they must take it.</p>
            <p class="smallText">If a player moves their piece to the back of their opponent's board, the piece will be crowned a King.</p>
            <br>
            <p class="smallText">
                Capture all your opponents pieces to win!
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h2>Join a friends game</h2>
            <br>
            <form action="boardPage.ejs" method="get">
                <input type="text" class="form-control centre" id="codeEntry" name="gameCode" placeholder="Enter game code here!" style="width: 50%;">
                <br>
                <input type="submit" value="Join Game!" class="btn btn-outline-success">
            </form>
            <br>

            <h2>Create your own game!</h2>
            <br>
            <form action="boardPage.ejs" method="post">
                <input type="hidden" name="requestedAction" value="createGame">
                <input type="submit" value="Create Game!" class="btn btn-outline-success">
            </form>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-3">
            <h4>High Scores</h4>
            <ol>
                <li><%= highScoresList[0].username%> - <%= highScoresList[0].wins%></li>
                <li><%= highScoresList[1].username%> - <%= highScoresList[1].wins%></li>
                <li><%= highScoresList[2].username%> - <%= highScoresList[2].wins%></li>
                <li><%= highScoresList[3].username%> - <%= highScoresList[3].wins%></li>
                <li><%= highScoresList[4].username%> - <%= highScoresList[4].wins%></li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>